name: KATE
description:
Kate Moss (KKAKE MOGGS)

Images similar to this were found in many of the ornately-decorated burial tombs of the ancient Mayans (250-900AD). Besides being London's queen of high fashion and one of the worlds most successful models, Moss was believed to have been worshipped by the Mayan people as the Deity of Beauty, Partying and addiction.

Beautiful 3-colour screen-print!
50x70cm (approx)
280GSM heavy cotton stock!
Deckled edges! You know you like!
Edition of 30!
Signed and numbered!

These prints ship in a sturdy shipping tube with Certificate of Authenticity. Please allow up to 10 days for delivery.

NOW WITH FREE WORLDWIDE SHIPPING! REGISTERED POST!

name: EHECATL MASK (twilight version) 1/25
description: EHECATL MASK (twilight version). Five Colour Screen-print, hand-finished on 300GSM Deckled edge somerset. 57 x 77cm. Signed and blind stamped Edition of 25. From my latest series of works, loosely based around Masoamerican gods, Aztec art and the 2012 doomsday predictions, I'm thrilled to announce a new screen-print in two colourways! It's been a while getting these looking just right. Five colours, three layers of hand-finishing, matt and gloss inks and blind-stamped. These are my most ambitious and most exciting screen-prints to date. I don't normally go on about things like this, but I'm so completely stoked with the result of these, and I hope you will be too. Blurring the lines between an original artwork and an edition, these prints feature layers of paint-splatter sandwiched between each layer of ink; A technique that's become synonymous with my paper originals and guarantees each print completely unique. Have a look at the 'making-of' process here. These prints ship in a sturdy shipping tube with Certificate of Authenticity. Please allow up to 10 days for delivery. NOW WITH FREE WORLDWIDE SHIPPING! REGISTERED POST!
